;a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1358:"<p><a href="https://github.com/johnnytee/bloggart/zipball/master">Download</a> my theme I created for my Google App Engine Bloggart blog.<br />\n<a href="http://github.com/Arachnid/bloggart"><br />\nBloggart</a> is an awesome open source blog created by Nick Johnson.</p>\n<p><strong>Features:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>HTML5 tags</li>\n<li>Built on the <a href="http://html5boilerplate.com/">HTML5 Boiler Plate Framework</a> by Paul Irish</li>\n<li>Mobile Layout using Media Queries</li>\n<li>Google Fonts</li>\n<li>Clean and Simple</li>\n<li>Canonical Urls&#8217;s</li>\n<p>To use canonicals urls add the code below to generators in generators.py</ul>\n<p>[python]template_vals[''canonical_url''] = &#8216;http://&#8217; + config.host + post.path[/python]</p>\n<p><strong>Front</strong><br />\n<a href="http://seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/06/2010-08-20_0905.jpeg"><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-587" title="2010-08-20_0905" src="http://seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/06/2010-08-20_0905-300x243.jpg" alt="" width="300" height="243" /></a></p>\n<p><strong>Admin</strong><br />\n<a href="http://seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/06/2010-08-20_0906.jpeg"><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-588" title="2010-08-20_0906" src="http://seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/06/2010-08-20_0906-300x247.jpg" alt="" width="300" height="247" /></a></p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:55:"http://seedprod.com/free-html5-theme-for-bloggart/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"0";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:6;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:41:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n\n		\n		\n			\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:5:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:49:"How to blog in real time with Google’s Feed API";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:157:"http://seedprod.com/how-to-blog-in-real-time-with-googles-feed-api/?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=how-to-blog-in-real-time-with-googles-feed-api";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:76:"http://seedprod.com/how-to-blog-in-real-time-with-googles-feed-api/#comments";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Fri, 07 Jan 2011 18:41:30 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:13:"Uncategorized";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:26:"http://seedprod.com/?p=513";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:323:"Google&#8217;s version 2 of their popular ajax feed api now can display PubSubHubbub enabled feeds in real-time. Using this api we can now easy blog in real time without polling. I&#8217;m going to show you how to set-up the example at the bottom of the page on your website. First you&#8217;ll need to configure your [...]";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:4:"John";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:3275:"<p>Google&#8217;s version 2 of their popular <a href="http://http://code.google.com/apis/ajaxfeeds/">ajax feed api</a> now can display <a href="http://code.google.com/p/pubsubhubbub/">PubSubHubbub</a> enabled feeds in real-time. Using this api we can now easy blog in real time without polling. I&#8217;m going to show you how to set-up the example at the bottom of the page on your website.</p>\n<p>First you&#8217;ll need to configure your blog or website to publish a pubsubhubbub feed. If you&#8217;re using a WordPress self hosted blog there are a few <a href="http://wordpress.org/extend/plugins/search.php?q=pubsubhubbub&amp;sort=">plugins</a> to choose from that will automatically do this for you. If you are on WordPress.com, Tumblr or Posterous then you&#8217;re already publishing a PubSubHubbub enabled feed. For <a href="http://www.feedburner.com/">Feedburner</a> feeds enable their service called &#8220;PingShot&#8221; under the publicize tab. The &#8220;PingShot&#8221; service will enable pubsubhubub on your feed but be aware the that FeedBurner is not real-time from your blog to their service. Otherwise consult the <a href="http://code.google.com/p/pubsubhubbub/">documentation</a> on how to add it to your site&#8217;s feed.</p>\n<p>Now that you are able to publish a real-time feed we want to consume that feed and display it to our readers with the Google Feed API for some real-time awesomeness. You&#8217;ll need to add the following javascript to include the Google Feed code to your site. Visit the Google Feed API site to <a href="http://code.google.com/apis/feed/push/">apply</a> for a Version 2 API key.</p>\n<pre class="prettyprint ">&lt;script type=&quot;text/javascript&quot; src=&quot;http://www.google.com/jsapi?key=AIzaSyBWk2VmSTr0NZEcYvE7o11A7Rkl4gRF-LY&quot;&gt;&lt;/script&gt;\n</pre>\n<p>Add a UL tag to your page where you want to display your feed and give it an id that you can reference.</p>\n<p>[javascript]&lt;ul id=&quot;real-time-feed&quot;&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;[/javascript]</p>\n<p>Next add your callback function and the feed(s) you&#8217;d like to subscribe to.</p>\n<p>[javascript]&lt;script type=&quot;text/javascript&quot;&gt;<br />\n  google.setOnLoadCallback(example_onLoadOfFeedApi);<br />\n  function example_onLoadOfFeedApi() {<br />\n    var feed1 = new    google.feeds.push.Feed(&quot;http://pubsubhubbub-example-app.appspot.com/feed&quot;);<br />\n    feed1.includeHistoricalEntries(3);<br />\n    feed1.subscribe(example_renderFeeds)<br />\n  }<br />\n&lt;/script&gt;[/javascript]</p>\n<p>Finally display the response you get from the callback. In this example I&#8217;m using jQuery to prepend a LI tag to the unordered list we created earlier.</p>\n<p>[javascript]function example_renderFeeds(response) {<br />\n    var entries = response.feed.entries;<br />\n    for (var i = 0; i &amp;lt; entries.length; i++) {<br />\n      jQuery(&amp;quot;#real-time-feed&amp;quot;).prepend(&amp;quot;&amp;lt;li&amp;gt;&lt;a href=&quot;&amp;quot;+entries[i].link+&amp;quot;&quot;&gt;&quot;+entries[i].title+&quot;&lt;/a&gt;&amp;lt;/li&amp;gt;&amp;quot;)<br />\n    }<br />\n  }[/javascript]</p>\n<h2>Demo not working? View the screencast.</h2>\n<p><iframe src="http://www.screenr.com/embed/G40" width="650" height="396" frameborder="0"></iframe></p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:72:"http://seedprod.com/how-to-blog-in-real-time-with-googles-feed-api/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"0";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml