(1, 1, '2012-01-09 21:05:04', '2012-01-09 21:05:04', 'Welcome to WordPress. This is your first post. Edit or delete it, then start blogging!', 'Hello world!', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'hello-world', '', '', '2012-01-09 21:05:04', '2012-01-09 21:05:04', '', 0, 'http://1stsocial.com.au//?p=1', 0, 'post', '', 1),
(2, 1, '2012-01-09 21:05:04', '2012-01-09 21:05:04', 'This is an example page. It''s different from a blog post because it will stay in one place and will show up in your site navigation (in most themes). Most people start with an About page that introduces them to potential site visitors. It might say something like this:\n\n<blockquote>Hi there! I''m a bike messenger by day, aspiring actor by night, and this is my blog. I live in Los Angeles, have a great dog named Jack, and I like pi&#241;a coladas. (And gettin'' caught in the rain.)</blockquote>\n\n...or something like this:\n\n<blockquote>The XYZ Doohickey Company was founded in 1971, and has been providing quality doohickies to the public ever since. Located in Gotham City, XYZ employs over 2,000 people and does all kinds of awesome things for the Gotham community.</blockquote>\n\nAs a new WordPress user, you should go to <a href="http://1stsocial.com.au//wp-admin/">your dashboard</a> to delete this page and create new pages for your content. Have fun!', 'Sample Page', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'sample-page', '', '', '2012-01-09 21:05:04', '2012-01-09 21:05:04', '', 0, 'http://1stsocial.com.au//?page_id=2', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(42, 1, '2012-03-14 05:44:09', '2012-03-14 05:44:09', '<img class="alignright size-medium wp-image-70" title="facebook-logo-1" src="http://1stsocial.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2012/03/facebook-logo-1-300x166.jpg" alt="" width="300" height="166" />According to the statistics, Facebook now has 850 million users world wide. That is a huge potential platform for marketing your business or product, but perhaps more importantly it is a potentially disastrous demographic to ignore.\r\n\r\nIn the USA, United Kingdom, Europe and Australia, between 60% and 70% of the whole population is on Facebook. That means that between 60% and 70% of your current and potential future client base is on Facebook, and if you don’t engage them, someone else will.\r\n\r\nSimply setting up a Facebook page or profile won’t cut it anymore, so 1stSocial helps you to develop unique and dynamic ways of not only interacting with your customers and audience, but of also delivering your product and brand to them. Facebook Marketing is more than just putting your URL somewhere or purchasing advertising space; it is about capturing the attention and imagination of your audience, and keeping them engaged so you stay relevant.\r\n\r\nOn top of that, why not use our unique Facebook Recruitment system next time you need to hire someone who gets your company and it''s goals? Or to power your Recruitment business?\r\n\r\nWe take this Facebook strategy a step further and help you connect your Facebook presence to your physical world, through the use of <a title="QR Codes" href="/qr-codes/">QR Codes</a>, smartphones and other technology, and integrate your new Facebook success into your current business strategy.', 'Facebook', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'facebook-marketing', '', '', '2012-03-16 03:08:36', '2012-03-16 03:08:36', '', 0, 'http://1stsocial.com.au/?page_id=42', 0, 'page', '', 0),
