(16, 2, '2013-04-05 06:06:10', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Project Engineer - 2 years experience ideally in waste water treatment process, needed for leader in design &amp; delivery of waste water solutions.\n<ul>\n	<li>Circa $70K plus super</li>\n	<li>Market Leader - water industry</li>\n	<li>Brisbane Office or work from home</li>\n</ul>\nOur client is a market leader in the manufacture of commercial scale water treatment and wastewater recycling systems. With activity in Australia and growth in overseas markets, they are entering a strong growth phase and are looking for the skills and aptitude of an experienced Project Engineer who enjoys the full circle process.\n\nYou will have 2+ years professional engineering design experience coupled with a degree in Mechanical Engineering. Your past experience may include exposure to the design of wastewater plants including process, hydraulic and mechanical/electrical components. An understanding of technical aspects of wastewater treatment in a variety of decentralized wastewater treatment technologies and water treatment technologies would be advantageous along with your ability to develop functional specifications for water and wastewater treatment systems. Your love of new technology will keep you interested in assessing new treatment technologies/processes and assisting in applying them to practical ecologically sustainable designs.\nReporting to the General Manager and working closely with a senior Engineer and small team of key staff, your main responsibilities will be Support to the team of onsite Treatment plant operators, trend analysis, identification of improved design/process and delivery of changes to standard product delivery whilst liaising with the client and coordinating all relevant subcontractors.\nYou will also conduct ongoing research and product/system development to meet evolving market opportunities and demands as well as continuous improvement focus across your areas of responsibility.\nYou will have excellent time management skills and the self discipline to ensure that you can manage the coordination of several projects concurrently. Attention to detail, initiative and accountability are all a must along with the flexibility to travel to remote sites\nIf you are looking for a role where you can make a difference, in a company that ismaking a difference - this is your next long term challenge.\nPlease click on the ‘Apply Now’ button below to submit your confidential application or telephone Suzanne Whitmarsh on (03) 8617 8110 for further information. Please see ‘Job Search'' on www.facebook.com/1stexecutive where you can apply and also register your details.', 'Project Engineer - Water', '', 'draft', 'closed', 'closed', '', '', '', '', '2013-04-05 06:06:10', '2013-04-05 06:06:10', '', 0, 'http://template.jobs.1stsocial.com.au/?post_type=jobs&#038;p=16', 0, 'jobs', '', 0);
